  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I know if some one has read my direct message on instagram?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Instagram does not provide a direct feature to show if someone has read your direct message (DM), unlike some other messaging apps that have read receipts. However, there are a few indirect ways to gauge if your message might have been seen:\n\n1. **Activity Status**: If the person's activity status is enabled, you might see \"Active Now\" or \"Active X minutes ago\" under their name in the chat. This doesn\u2019t confirm they read your message, but it indicates they were recently active on Instagram.\n\n2. **Seen by All**: If you send a photo or video to a group chat, you might see a \"Seen by\" list under your message. However, this feature isn\u2019t available for text messages or in one-on-one chats.\n\n3. **Typing Indicator**: If the person starts typing a response, you'll see a typing indicator (\"...\" bubble). This suggests they've at least opened the chat and seen your message.\n\n4. **Profile Visits**: If you notice an increase in profile visits or story views from that person after sending the message, it might suggest they've seen your message and are checking out your profile.\n\n5. **Response**: The most definitive way is if they respond to your message. Even a reaction (like a heart or a haha) can indicate they've read it.\n\nRemember, none of these methods are foolproof indicators that your message has been read, especially if the person is choosing to ignore your message or isn\u2019t very active on Instagram. Instagram might update its features, so it's always a good idea to check the latest information directly from Instagram's help center or support pages.",
